# Service Layer

## ClinicService facade

`ClinicService` is the single facade for all domain operations (except User). `ClinicServiceImpl`:

- Is annotated `@Service`
- Constructor-injects all six repository interfaces: `PetRepository`, `VetRepository`, `OwnerRepository`, `VisitRepository`, `SpecialtyRepository`, `PetTypeRepository`
- Applies `@Transactional` to every method (`readOnly = true` for queries)
- Contains NO business logic — it delegates directly to repositories

## UserService

`UserService` / `UserServiceImpl` is separate, handling only `User` persistence. It validates that users have at least one role and auto-prefixes role names with `ROLE_`.

## Rules

- ALL controller→repository access MUST go through `ClinicService` or `UserService` — never inject a repository directly into a controller
- Read methods: `@Transactional(readOnly = true)`
- Write methods: `@Transactional`
- Handle `ObjectRetrievalFailureException` and `EmptyResultDataAccessException` by returning `null` for not-found cases
